    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "`crypto.Sign` provides plain ECDSA operations. The 27/28 value is a standard in Ethereum, carried over from bitcoin. It has nothing to do with ECDSA. You will need to manually modify the V value of the returned signature to match the format you desire (either 27/28 or EIP-155).",
